events.name: Introduction to Reinforcement Learning using TF 2.0 - Samiran Roy
events.description:
Pic Credit : Samuel

This is a colloboration event between GDG Mysore and TFUG Mysore

Topic :

Introduction to Reinforcement Learning using TF 2.0 - Samiran Roy

Its Youtube Live event . Link will be available upon RSVP.

Abstract: Reinforcement learning(RL) needs no introduction - we have seen robots teaching themselves how to play soccer, learning how to drive, learning how to dance by watching a youtube video, beating professional teams at Dota 2, and beating world champions at Go.

RL was largely confined to academia for several decades and is now beginning to see some successful applications and products in the industry, in fields such as robotics, automated trading systems, manufacturing, energy, dialog systems and recommendation engines. For most companies, it is an exciting prospect due to the AI hype, however there is a lack of practical understanding/intuition on how/where to build RL models.

This talk will attempt to bridge that gap by giving a practical introduction to RL, focusing on intuitively presenting the ideas from a software dev/problem solving perspective. It will also serve as a “starter pack” for people looking to get into the field.

Bio: I am currently cofounding an early stage data driven startup called TildeHat.
Prior to this, I worked as a Senior Lead Data Scientist at Envestnet | Yodlee where I deployed Deep Learning, Reinforcement Learning, and Semi-Supervised learning-based products.

During my Masters at IIT Bombay, I spent my time developing deep learning, reinforcement learning, and computer vision software. I worked on a lot of cool AI - agents for self-driving cars, robot soccer, Atari games, and Carrom. As a part of my MTech thesis, I developed a Multi-Armed-Bandit framework for autonomous agents to supervise their own training.

events.name: Automatically Refactoring and  Crafting quality code in Python (PyCharm)
events.description:
Pic Credit : Mohammed Shafi

Its colloborative event between GDG Mysuru , GDG Bangalore , Bangpypers and JetBrains India

Kindly subscribe to the channel for sessions related to AI every week

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChr1xW6wSq4sxUgAlgv9PZQ?sub_confirmation=1

Speaker 1 :

Topic : Automatically Refactoring Python Code (with PyCharm)

Abstract : As part of Agile technical practices, refactoring is now a mainstay practice in most development projects. This session is all about making it automated, i.e., how deep understanding of refactoring and tools can help automate most of the refactoring tasks!

In this session, we'll cover how to identify smells automatically, how to auto refactor, refactor to functional programming, and how to perform complex refactorings without breaking the working code.

Demo examples are in Python using PyCharm.

Speaker: Ganesh Samartham (LinkedIn profile: https://www.linkedin.com/in/ganeshsamarthyam/).

Youtube Live URL : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5ezC0PDKMR8

Brief bio: Ganesh is co-founder of CodeOps & KonfHub. His last book was “Refactoring for Software Design Smells: Managing Technical Debt” published by Morgan Kaufmann/Elsevier with translations in Korean and Chinese.

Speaker 2 :

Title: Crafting Quality Code in PyCharm

Youtube Live URL : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J-AmQlPqhWo

PyCharm has amazing capabilities for automated code generation & completion, automated analysis and refactoring. This session helps you develop quality code in lightning speed with (close-to) zero effort in Pycharm.

Pre-requisites:
* Working knowledge in programming with Python
* PyCharm installed (preferably the latest version)

About the presenter: Srushith is the Head of Engineering at KonfHub. For the last 2 years, he has been working on developing and architecting Serverless applications using Python and AWS. He is an avid presenter at tech conferences, meetups and an active community contributor. His LinkedIn profile: https://www.linkedin.com/in/srushith/

upcoming.name: Drafting Smart India Hackathon Proposal- Roadmap to be a National Winner
upcoming.description:
Kindly subscribe to the youtube channel for tech videos every week.

hhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UChr1xW6wSq4sxUgAlgv9PZQ?sub_confirmation=1

It is a colloborative event between GDG Mysore and GDG Bangalore

Topic : Drafting Smart India Hackathon Proposal- Roadmap to be a National Winner

Youtube Live URL : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UhWTxyUXR_I

Abstract:
Smart India Hackathon is a nationwide initiative to provide students a platform to solve some of the pressing problems we face in our daily lives, and thus inculcate a culture of product innovation and a mindset of problem-solving. It is being organized since 2017 every year by MHRD.
Every year 2 Lakh+ students, that is 35,000 teams participate. In total 37,000+ ideas are submitted. Out of which only 1300+ teams go for the grand finale, which means 0.037 probability of selection.It sums up as approximately 4 students out of 100 are selected. Not done yet, after reaching the grand finale, only 1 team in the particular problem
statement secures the national winner position.

Now, the question arises, What to do exactly to reach the grand finale of SIH?

Are the technical skills or a special method of presenting your mind on paper, will help us to reach there?

This session will give a complete reference of what it actually takes you to reach the SIH Grand Finale. What should you write in the proposal? How to structure and organize your content?

Agenda :

1. What is SIH?
2. Evaluation Criteria
3. 5 question rule
4. Concentration rule / Reading rule
5. How to draft proposal (intro)
6. Sample ppt by SIH
7. Study of content
8. Structure of proposal
9. Q/A concept
10. Screen shots or pictures
11. Block Diagrams, wireframes, design models, DFDs, etc
12. Use Case diagrams
13. Question from attendees

Speaker Bio :

Web Portfolio:
Link: http://bit.ly/kyratna
LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyratna/
Ph: +91 –[masked]

Yashoratna is a pre-final year student pursuing Bachelor of Technology from KIET Group Of Institutions in Computer Science and Engineering.
He has interned for NITI AAYOG, Punjab National Bank and GeeksforGeeks on various roles.He is working on multiple technologies like Object-Oriented Techniques, Machine Learning,NLP, OpenCV etc. His strengths are Data Structures, Databases, Algorithms, its Optimization,and coding.He is the winner of Smart India Hackathon 2019 Software (SIH'19), and selected for the grand finale of SIH'20 as well.
He is moving towards building his career in the IT world. He believes in never stopping, work as a team, build, learn, and code.

answers.answer:
Passionate about new technology.

Being a CA student, I also am looking forward to integrating technology in my work and profession to a much greater extent.
Hoping these events will be a foundation for everything.

answers.question: What excites you the most about Technology?
answers.answer:
New things and it's applications!!
People wouldn't have even thought about such stuff and it's already there in front of us.
One thing open door to many other doors and the possibility are endless.
What was fiction few years ago is becoming reality one by one.
And using such technology in a country like India and its development, excites me and give goosebumps thinking about the betterment of the country and the positive impact on lives of people.
